investigation.title: Metagenomic analysis of feces from mice flown on the RR-6 mission
investigation.description: The objective of the Rodent Research-6 (RR-6) study was to evaluate muscle atrophy in mice during spaceflight and to test the efficacy of a novel therapeutic to mitigate muscle wasting. The experiment involved an implantable subcutaneous nanochannel delivery system (nDS; between scapula), which delivered the drug formoterol (FMT; a selective Î²2 adrenoceptor agonist), over the course of time.
